main event: A single unidentified object resembling a satellite was observed over the Matagorda area at 1900Z on November 19, 1964.
interesting points: The object was tracked crossing the Guadalcanal area at 174.79W at 1900Z.
The object's position was reported at 33.39N 164.06E.
The object was observed at a medium altitude with a positive angle of 23 degrees.
The object was traveling on a course of 140 degrees.
The weather was clear with a sea state of moderate 2 ft swells and a wind of 12 knots from the southeast.
sighted object: A single unidentified object resembling a satellite
